arch:property.oc:show_val: Arbitrary unit of midden deposit outside of the west wall of building 3. Sample 3 was completely recorded, the rest had just the identifiable bones recorded. The unit was similar to 8178, 8253 and the other midden units. High fragmentation, ca. 5% carbonised, high proportion of the bone had been digested. This unit seems to have a slightly better representation of upper limb bones compared to the others that are all dominated by digested carpals/tarsals and phalanges. Overall these units have a wider species representation compared to the internal contexts, although the sample of bones identifiable to species is significantly greater. NR 2006: A bone point fragment has emerged from the figurine stash, from Sample 3 >4mm flotation.

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
